26/04/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis will visit Washington and meet with US President George W. Bush on 20 May, it was announced Monday (25 April).
The trip will focus on issues related to trans-Atlantic ties as well as the situations in Southeast Europe and the Middle East.
Greek Defence Minister Spilios Spiliotopoulos kicked off a three-day visit to the United States on Monday, meeting with counterpart Donald Rumsfeld to discuss bilateral co-operation in the military sector.
(Kathimerini - 26/04/05;
ANA - 25/04/05)
